SME (Sharing, Mind, Enjoyment) App, A Pilot Project is part of the Community-based Mental Wellness Project for Adolescents and Adults, which aims at promoting sharing, mind and enjoyment and enhancing mental wellbeing.

 The Mental Wellness Project is financially supported by the Health Care and Promotion Fund from Food and Health Bureau and led by the School of Public Health, University of Hong Kong (HKU).

 This project primarily aims to promote the SME related behaviors of adolescents through the App.

 The evaluation will be conducted during the programme implementation stage.

 The effectiveness of the intervention, as well as the level of participation and ratings for the intervention, will be evaluated.

